PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1782188270
OL,3,CBurnham to give speech on economy
OL,4,Cafter Starmer resignation clears way
OL,5,Cto No 10
OL,7,FSir Keir said he would ask Labour's
OL,8,Fruling National Executive Committee
OL,9,F(NEC) to set out a timetable that
OL,10,Fwould see a new leader in place by the
OL,11,Ftime Parliament returns from its
OL,12,Fsummer recess on September 1.
OL,14,FBut the anointing of a new leader
OL,15,Fcould come much sooner, with
OL,16,Fnominations closing on July 16.
OL,18,FPotential candidates have until then
OL,19,Fto amass the support of at least 81
OL,20,FLabour MPs.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
